From: Arran Cudbard-Bell <a.cudbardb@freeradius.org>
Subject: [PATCH] solaris: fix POST(sys_port) PORT_GETN packed-return decoding

portfs(PORT_GETN) on illumos packs its int64_t return as a union rval
(see <sys/systm.h>):
  low  32 bits (r_val1) = nget (events written), or -1 on hard error
  high 32 bits (r_val2) = 0 on success, ETIME on timeout

portfs is registered SE_64RVAL so RES holds the full packed int64_t.
See illumos uts/common/fs/portfs/port.c portfs() PORT_GETN case and
the libc unpacking in lib/libc/port/gen/event_port.c port_getn().

The existing POST handler treated RES as a flat count of events.  On
ETIME RES is (62 << 32), and RES * sizeof(port_event_t) is a TB-scale
range that, when fed to POST_MEM_WRITE, corrupts memcheck's shadow
tracking and panics:

  Memcheck: the 'impossible' happened:
    create_MC_Chunk: shadow area is accessible

Hard errors don't reach the POST handler (kernel goes through
set_errno() and SUCCESS is false), so we only need to handle the
success/ETIME packed return: extract the low 32 bits as nget.
---
 coregrind/m_syswrap/syswrap-solaris.c | 7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/coregrind/m_syswrap/syswrap-solaris.c b/coregrind/m_syswrap/syswrap-solaris.c
index abc..def 100644
--- a/coregrind/m_syswrap/syswrap-solaris.c
+++ b/coregrind/m_syswrap/syswrap-solaris.c
@@ -7802,9 +7802,12 @@ POST(sys_port)
    case VKI_PORT_GET:
       POST_MEM_WRITE(ARG3, sizeof(vki_port_event_t));
       break;
-   case VKI_PORT_GETN:
-      POST_MEM_WRITE(ARG3, RES * sizeof(vki_port_event_t));
+   case VKI_PORT_GETN: {
+      UInt nget = (UInt)(RES & 0xFFFFFFFFu);
+      if (nget > 0)
+         POST_MEM_WRITE(ARG3, (UInt)nget * sizeof(vki_port_event_t));
       break;
+   }
    case VKI_PORT_ALERT:
    case VKI_PORT_DISPATCH:
       break;
